WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.440
We all know Taylor Swift is having a massive year. Her heirs tour is expected to bring in 3.6 billion

00:00:05.440 --> 00:00:10.720
and this visualization behind me was made in R so you can actually make this yourself with code.

00:00:10.720 --> 00:00:15.440
I didn't make this, my co-worker Isabella did, but she's going to show you how you can make this too

00:00:15.440 --> 00:00:21.760
in Cordova. In R you can create a tree map using ggplot2 and the tree mapify package. First you

00:00:21.760 --> 00:00:27.280
have to convert your data frame into the right format to visualize those relationships using

00:00:27.280 --> 00:00:32.799
the tree mapify function which I do here. Next I initialize the ggplot2 that I want to create

00:00:34.639 --> 00:00:40.480
then I add my tree map. I can even add a custom image if I want to.

00:00:44.320 --> 00:00:48.799
Finally I finish adding all the details to the ggplot2 that I want

00:00:49.599 --> 00:00:53.599
and when I use ggsave it's going to save this image.

